of outpouching","Predominantly right-sided distribution in Western populations"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDiverticulosis is characterised by herniation of colonic mucosa and submucosa through the muscular layer. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased intraluminal pressure\u003C/strong\u003E is a key factor in the pathogenesis, leading to herniation at weak points where blood vessels penetrate the circular muscle layer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emuscular layer\u003C/strong\u003E is actually absent at the site of outpouching, not thickened. The condition shows a \u003Cstrong\u003Epredominantly left-sided distribution\u003C/strong\u003E in Western populations, particularly affecting the sigmoid colon. Diverticula involve only the mucosa and submucosa, not \u003Cstrong\u003Eall layers of the bowel wall\u003C/strong\u003E. \u003Cstrong\u003EColonic transit time\u003C/strong\u003E is typically increased, not decreased, due to altered motility patterns.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERisk factors include low-fibre diet, aging, and altered colonic motility. Complications can include diverticulitis, bleeding, and perforation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diverticulosis is characterised by outpouchings of colonic mucosa and submucosa through the muscular layer due to increased intraluminal pressure","Risk factors for diverticulosis include low-fibre diet, aging, and altered colonic motility","Most common locations for diverticulosis are sigmoid and descending colon"],"references":["Piscopo N, Ellul P. Diverticular Disease: A Review on Pathophysiology and Recent Evidence. Ulster Med J. 2020 Sep;89(2):83-88. Epub 2020 Oct 21. PMID: 33093692; PMCID: PMC7576390.","Feuerstein JD, Falchuk KR. Diverticulosis and Diverticulitis. Mayo Clin Proc. 2016 Aug;91(8):1094-104. doi: 10.1016/j.mayocp.2016.03.012. Epub 2016 May 5. PMID: 27156370.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52597"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15395"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21284"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21284","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21284"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/m5JouejYGtR1mODzbrfzSn5KVwqfsN.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/m5JouejYGtR1mODzbrfzSn5KVwqfsN.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":374,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52597","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52597"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T18:52:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T18:52:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8086"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67141"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (ident